{"questionId":"21547","questionHtml":"<p>The diagram shows two cylindrical wires, X and Y. Wire X has a length <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>l</mi></math></em>, a diameter <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi></math></em>, and a&nbsp;resistivity <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ρ</mi></math>. Wire Y has a length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>l</mi></math>, a diameter of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>d</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>and a resistivity of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>ρ</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/57ccda58347d68dcc8c4eb82dd5a406f62451bca.png\"></p>\n<p>What is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mtext>resistance&nbsp;of&nbsp;X</mtext><mtext>resistance&nbsp;of&nbsp;Y</mtext></mfrac></math>?</p>\n<p>A. 4</p>\n<p>B. 2</p>\n<p>C. 0.5</p>\n<p>D. 0.25</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>D</p>","meta":{"questionId":"21547","referenceCode":"21M.1.SL.TZ2.18","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"The diagram shows two cylindrical wires, X and Y. Wire X has a length l, a diameter d, and a resistivity ρ. Wire Y has a length 2l, a diameter of d2and a resistivity of ρ2. What is","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"18","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism","5.2 – Heating effect of electric currents","Core","Topic 5: Electricity and magnetism"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}